42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"Myzu218JY2"}],"key":"SdSgufyYu4"}],"key":"VXNlWs57ea"}],"key":"cLOHsV6MBE"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Grading rubrics will usually be provided with each module.\nIt is expected that students in this course will have a wide range of prior experience\nand ability, and grading will aim to reflect learning and effort in the course.\nThis course is not graded “on a curve” compared to other students.\nGrades will reflect relative individual learning and improvement from earlier benchmarks.\nIt is certainly possible for all students to receive high grades in this course\nif all of you show mastery of the material and completely attempt all assignments.\nHowever, high competency that does not reflect learning gains or the stylistic expectations of this\ncourse may score quite poorly. Our course prizes concise, semantic code supported by clear\nand insightful text and figures.","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"BlIT8mZGsF"}],"key":"sB9HhBioqu"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All assignments are due by immediately ","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"key":"yJ17G8Vzmy"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"before","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"key":"sDyGsGFG8o"}],"key":"w7U8eEMf8f"},{"type":"text","value":" the start of class on the day indicated. Assignments should be submitted as instructed.","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"key":"U6zo0kQ5dO"}],"key":"dKoLwr35Rn"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Make-up policy","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"key":"VRyxy7ghh1"}],"identifier":"make-up-policy","label":"Make-up policy","html_id":"make-up-policy","implicit":true,"key":"eoMtLO4Mtl"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Late assignments may be docked 20% and will not be accepted more than 48\nhours late except in cases of genuine emergencies\nor in cases where this has been discussed and approved in\nadvance. This policy is based on the idea that in order to learn how to\nuse computers well, students should be working with them at multiple times\neach week. Time has been allotted in class for working on assignments and\nstudents are expected to work on them outside of class. It is intended\nthat you should have finished as much of the assignment as you can based\non what we have covered in class by the following class period. Therefore,\neven if something unexpected happens at the last minute you should already\nbe close to done with the assignment. This policy also allows rapid\nfeedback to be provided to students by returning assignments quickly.","position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":59,"column":1}},"key":"gTHfU7qdPx"}],"key":"LBEbitGYQU"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Code of Conduct","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"I5RJkxeKyP"}],"identifier":"code-of-conduct","label":"Code of Conduct","html_id":"code-of-conduct","implicit":true,"key":"xwpW7xkgn3"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":80,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Our course is committed to providing a respectful and welcoming\nenvironment to all participants.  Please review the\n","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"GiARXsxH4P"},{"type":"link","url":"http://todogroup.org/opencodeofconduct/","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open Code of Conduct","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"RhA6dv3lTp"}],"urlSource":"http://todogroup.org/opencodeofconduct/","key":"nP6sdF2ydT"},{"type":"text","value":"\nguidelines for respectful and harassment-free conduct. To report\nan incident or request more information, contact the UC Berkeley\n","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"Qc91ITrLWq"},{"type":"link","url":"https://ophd.berkeley.edu","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Office for the Prevention of Harassment and Discrimination","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"BU9zB1hLlB"}],"urlSource":"https://ophd.berkeley.edu","key":"OshwzHK8st"},{"type":"text","value":" by emailing ","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"LalEcocW8L"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"ask_ophd@berkeley.edu","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"ZdbbDHDqo2"},{"type":"text","value":" or by phone (510) 643-7985.","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"Ea7sOjHw3V"}],"key":"MI1PIX40Xe"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":82,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learning Cooperatively","position":{"start":{"line":82,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"key":"N7mqlnDSHf"}],"identifier":"learning-cooperatively","label":"Learning Cooperatively","html_id":"learning-cooperatively","implicit":true,"key":"w5MDefVegI"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I encourage you to discuss all of the course activities with your friends\nand classmates and your instructional team as you are working on them.\nYou will definitely learn more\nin this class if you work with others than if you do not. Ask questions,\nanswer questions, and share ideas liberally. ","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"key":"I5OObunhLm"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Please identify your\ncollaborators by name on all assignments","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"key":"WQ3agZjPTi"}],"key":"OJL39DPm0U"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"key":"Z1aAHq1CUg"}],"key":"A7VSsVBCTD"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since you’re working collaboratively, keep your project partner and the\ncourse instructor informed. If some medical or personal emergency takes\nyou away from the course for an extended period, or if you decide to drop\nthe course for any reason, please don’t just disappear silently! You\nshould inform your project partner, so that nobody is depending on you\nto do something you can’t finish.","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"IA5XkVVbkJ"}],"key":"rEzwO9NeNN"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generative AI","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"key":"WZpXQDDFjs"}],"identifier":"generative-ai","label":"Generative AI","html_id":"generative-ai","implicit":true,"key":"GJfvl6THSx"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generative AI is very much a part of the modern data science landscape and\nwill be a part of our course.  This technology also raises legal, ethical\nand environmental issues, as technology has done before. We will seek to\naddress and discuss both the opportunities and challenges through hands-on\nexperience with examples of this technology.","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"key":"bS3bIBznuB"}],"key":"NSxl91LYAW"},{"type":"comment","value":"\nThis course will explore not\nonly how generative AI can assist (and fail) in programming tasks, but how\nwe can run language models ourselves and build th into applications safely\nand reliably.\n","key":"DloMMrwah9"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Quiz/Exam Policy","position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"key":"PGfAMr7Spv"}],"identifier":"quiz-exam-policy","label":"Quiz/Exam Policy","html_id":"quiz-exam-policy","implicit":true,"key":"RU6LAW7nhc"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are no quizzes or in-class exams in this course.","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"uHxQxjQGj3"}],"key":"etozPKL4nx"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Course Technology","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"UFkMhEhQqk"}],"identifier":"course-technology","label":"Course Technology","html_id":"course-technology","implicit":true,"key":"OVA5vGzWln"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Students should bring a laptop and charger to each class. You do not need a\nfancy machine -- any device with a 